1) Open your Copilot chat

Go to the conversation you want to save:
    Copilot Free → https://copilot.microsoft.com
    Copilot 365 → https://www.microsoft365.com/copilot
Make sure the full chat is visible on the screen.

2) Open the browser tools
Press:
    Windows: F12
    Mac: ⌥ Option + ⌘ Command + I
A side panel will appear.
Click the Console tab.

3) Copy the script
Choose the version you need:
    Copilot 365 script
    Copilot Free script
Open the file, select all the text, and copy it.

4) Paste the script into the Console
Go back to the browser, click inside the Console, paste the script, and press Enter.
The script will start running automatically.

5) Wait for the export to finish
The script will:
    Scroll through the entire chat
    Capture every message
    Ask you to confirm two dates
    Generate the export files

When it finishes, your browser will download:
    One HTML file (full chat)
    One JSONL file (structured data)

You’re done.
